definition.value: A glycosyl alditol consisting of a beta-D-galactopyranose residue and a D-mannitol residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An L-xylofuranose that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.

An amino pentasaccharide that is beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 of the mannosyl residue have been glycosylated by beta-D-xylopyranosyl and  alpha-D-mannopyranosyl residues respectively.
A beta-D-Glcp-(1->6)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A purine nucleobase found in humans and other organisms.
